gomodel:SYNGO_5065  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099055 replaced by GO:0045211" , "Rationale: Figure 2: Subcellular fractionation patterns of Clmp protein in the rat brain showed Clmp is enriched in synaptic, but not PSD, fractions. In HEK293T cells, co-immunoprecipitation of Clmp and PSD-95 (DLG4) showed these proteins do not form a complex (Clmp relatives like IgSF11 are known to interact with PSD-95). Clmp does not have a functional PDZ-binding motif.\n\nFigure 3: \"Clmp deletion leads to changes in AMPAR, KAR, and NMDAR mEPSCs in Clmp-/- CA3 neurons; increased frequency and amplitude of AMPAR mEPSCs, increased frequency, amplitude, and decay time constant of KAR mEPSCs, and decreased frequency of NMDAR mEPSCs.\"\n\nFigure 5: Extracellular and cytoplasmic regions of Clmp interact with AMPARs and KARs.\n\nFigure 7: Increased extrasynaptic KAR currents and decreased extrasynaptic NMDAR currents in Clmp-/- hippocampal CA3 neurons.\n\nBased on the known transmembrane topology of this protein, \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was selected.. Experimental description: M&M: \"The Clmp-/- mice used in the present study were originally generated by Genentech, Inc. (Tang et al., 2010).\"\n\nantibody:\n\"Peptides containing mouse Clmp (aa 345-373) were used to immunize guinea pigs (2090). The specificity of anti-Clmp antibodies (2090) was confirmed by immunoblot experiments using Clmp-/- whole-brain lysates.\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_5065" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

